          <source>When you have a successful or business-critical web app, you need to update it to respond to business changes, user demands, or security issues.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>But you can't allow service interruptions.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Suppose you work for a company that runs a popular social media web platform.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The user interface for this platform is set up as an ASP.NET Core MVC web app that's hosted in Azure App Service.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You regularly update the app's source code and roll out the updates to production.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>These updates occasionally cause problems when testers fail to catch bugs.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Also, service is briefly interrupted when you roll out an update, and then responsiveness is slow while the code is deployed and compiled.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You want a way to deploy a new version of the app without downtime or a service interruption.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You also want to be able to rapidly roll back a new deployment to the previous version if it causes problems.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Learning objectives</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this module, you will:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create a deployment slot as a staging environment in App Service.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use git to deploy a new version of a web app to a slot.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Configure which app settings are swapped and which are not swapped when you deploy a slot.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Swap slots to deploy a web app or roll back a deployment.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Prerequisites</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Basic experience deploying apps to App Service</source>
